Add a new multi-step intake wizard BEFORE the Section Library.

Goal: collect the minimum details needed to (1) personalize preview copy and (2) recommend the best sections for the user’s campground business model and conversion goal.

Wizard requirements:
- Stepper UI at top with clear progress (Step 1 of 4, etc.)
- Save user inputs as variables that can be reused across the builder (e.g., {{campground_name}}, {{primary_goal}})
- Validation: required fields show inline errors and prevent continuing
- “Back” and “Next” buttons, with a final “Continue to Section Library” button

Steps and fields:

Step 1 — Contact + Park Identity
- Campground Name * (text) placeholder: Pine Valley Campground
- Your Name * (text) placeholder: John Smith
- Email Address * (email) placeholder: john@example.com
- Phone Number (tel) placeholder: (705) 555-0123
- Current Website URL (url) placeholder: https://www.yourpark.com

Step 2 — Business Model
- Primary Business Model * (radio):
  - Seasonal Sites
  - Overnight Camping
  - Trailer Sales
  - Cottage Rentals
- Secondary Business Model (optional multi-select checkboxes, same list)

Step 3 — Goals + Audience
- Primary Goal * (radio):
  - Bookings
  - Inquiries
  - Trailer Leads
- Secondary Goal (optional select): same list
- Target audience (checkboxes):
  - Families
  - Couples
  - Snowbirds
  - Retirees
  - Outdoor adventurers

Step 4 — Messaging + Pain Points
- What are your pain points? (textarea) placeholder: “Outdated site, too many calls, hard to update…”
- What do you want to highlight? (textarea) placeholder: “New pool, theme weekends, big sites…”
- Anything else we should know? (textarea)

After Step 4, show a “Summary” screen and then enter the Section Library.

When the user reaches the Section Library:
- Personalize the top header: “Build {{campground_name}}’s homepage”
- Pre-select recommended sections based on Primary Business Model + Primary Goal
- Display a “Recommended for you” badge on the best-fit sections
- Allow user to change selections

